HEADWORD: Cystine
<hw>Cyst"ine</hw> <pr>(s?s"t?n; 104)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Cyst</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A white
crystalline substance, <chform>C3H7NSO2</chform>, containing sulphur,
occurring as a constituent of certain rare urinary calculi, and
occasionally found as a sediment in urine.</def><-- cysteine? -->⟦br⟧
